news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 20 commercial units without building use permission
news.para: The town planning and estate department teams also demolished 28,685 sq feet of illegal construction of 18 commercial properties located in various areas of the city.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate approves plan to raise up to Rs 1,500 crore
news.para: The board of directors of the company has approved raising of funds, aggregating upto Rs 1,500 crore through one or more Qualified Institutions Placement in one or more tranches, Indiabulls Real Estate said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: JK Paper's director buys Rs 250-crore Lutyens bungalow
news.para: Recently, Anil Gupta, chairman and managing director of KEI Industries, a cable and wire manufacturer, bought a 2,000-square yard property in Delhi's Shanti Niketan.

news.title: Greater Noida: Soon, you can rate upkeep in your society
news.para: Officials said the rating of a particular society would be done on the feedback received from its residents across 10 parameters such as sanitation, maintenance of lift, electric supply and common areas.

news.title: Bengaluru: 34,000 applicants in queue for housing scheme for poor
news.para: According to an official estimate, there are 4.3 lakh migrant families without their own house in Bengaluru city alone, and the scheme envisages building one lakh houses for the poor.

news.title: Mumbai: Government scraps 2016 housing scheme for mill workers
news.para: Awhad was responding to a question raised by Congress MLC Bhai Jagtap during question hour. Awhad said the scheme was to merge 160 sq ft rental flats and give them to the mill workers.

news.title: No registration of flats without Tamil Nadu RERA nod
news.para: Citing a September 2020 communique, the inspector general (registration) in a new letter to his subordinates has reminded SROs about the mandate.

news.title: Sky no longer the limit for Germany's 'Mainhattan' skyscraper boom
news.para: Dubbed "Mainhattan" by locals in a nod to its skyscrapers and location on the Main river, Germany's financial hub may be a far cry from New York in terms of nightlife, culture and banking but it did beat it to top a 2021 real estate bubble index.

news.title: Warburg Pincus closes $2.8 billion inaugural Asia real estate fund
news.para: The Warburg Pincus Asia Real Estate Fund is the second-largest fund dedicated to the sector in Asia, according to data provider Preqin. Blackstone Group raised $7.1 billion in the region's largest real estate fund in 2018, the data showed.

news.title: China Evergrande Group says will 'actively engage' with creditors
news.para: Evergrande, the world's most indebted developer with more than $300 billion of liabilities, including nearly $20 billion of international market bonds, was formally declared in default by ratings firms this month after it missed repayments.

news.title: China: Sinic Holdings warns of default on $250 million bond due in January 2022
news.para: Sinic said it did not have sufficient funds to pay the principal and last instalment of the senior unsecured note due on its maturity date - Jan. 24, 2022.

news.title: Motilal Oswal Real Estate plans to invest Rs 1,000 crore by March in realty projects
news.para: In a statement, Motilal Oswal Real Estate said that the company has cumulatively committed Rs 1,200 crore through its platform post the outbreak of COVID-19.

news.title: Sebi allows REITs to conduct unitholders' annual meetings virtually till Jun 2022
news.para: ​The circular came after Sebi received representations from REITs/InvITs to further extend the facility to conduct annual meetings and other meetings of unitholders through videoconferencing (VC) or through other audio-visual means (OAVM).

news.title: Over 39,000 from backward classes yet to get PMAY-G houses in Odisha
news.para: In reply to a query by Bargarh MP Suresh Pujari, Jyoti told the Parliament that of the 41.72 lakh households enlisted in Socio Economic and Caste Census (SECC) list of 2011 in Odisha, 18.75 lakh were verified as eligible by the state under PMAY-G as on December 16.

news.title: SWAMIH releases second instalment of stress fund to Capital Athena project in Greater Noida
news.para: “The builder had received the first instalment in May and after the satisfactory progress, SBICAP has released the second instalment. Sikka group has also received approval for the funding while funding for two more projects - Supercity and Jatasya is also under process,” said an authority official.
